ServiceDesk Plus is now treated as the source of truth for NUS devices: an `asset_tag` collision can no longer abort the sync. Placeholder asset_tags (`n/a`, `-`, etc.) and asset_tags duplicated across SDP records are normalized to empty on load, and a pre-sync reconcile pass resolves collisions with existing devices in SDP's favour — adopting the same physical device when the serial matches (stamping it with the SDP id), deleting a stale unclaimed NUS device otherwise, and never touching non-NUS/infrastructure devices.
